[2026-03-07T16:38:02Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014PT1ikPzHt4CdUp8WKq6kR","type":"tool_result","content":"total 52\ndrwxrwxr-x 13 agent agent 4096 Mar  3 19:35 .\ndrwxr-xr-x  1 agent agent 4096 Mar  7 16:33 ..\ndrwxrwxr-x  9 agent agent 4096 Mar  3 20:51 adapters\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  4 19:31 agent\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  6 21:19 config\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  6 22:04 domain\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  6 22:03 dsl\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  4 17:28 engine\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  2 20:15 evolution\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  3 20:10 logstream\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  7 02:45 orchestrator\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  3 23:40 ports\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Feb 27 16:12 protocol","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DjKJiL3pnVwWRgKQMqGBx3","session_id":"46174c86-2501-486a-9678-0ff3d3a9d495","uuid":"ad50cfdf-871e-4181-8244-cf54116c1047"}
[2026-03-07T16:38:02Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DjKJiL3pnVwWRgKQMqGBx3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile my comprehensive findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Agent Architecture Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase. Here's the complete agent architecture documentation:\n\n---\n\n## 1. AgentAdapter Interface/Port Definition\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`\n\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n\tName() string\n\tExecute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Simple, clean interface with only 2 methods\n- `Name()`: Returns the adapter's identifier (e.g., \"generic\", \"prompt\")\n- `Execute()`: Executes a single agent step inside a container\n  - Takes: context, step definition, and working directory\n  - Returns: step result name (string) and error\n  - Result is one of the step's declared `Results`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Existing Agent Adapter Implementations\n\n### 2.1 Generic Adapter (Script-based steps)\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`\n\n**Purpose:** Executes shell commands via `sh -c`\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Handles both `StepTypeScript` and `StepTypeAgent` with `run` config\n- Executes command in working directory\n- Captures combined stdout/stderr\n- Supports `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker in output to override exit code\n- Writes output to `.cloche/output/<step-name>.log`\n- Records execution history via `protocol.AppendHistory()`\n\n**Config Keys:**\n- `run`: Shell command to execute\n\n**Result Logic:**\n- Exit 0 + output = \"success\" (or marked result)\n- Exit non-zero = \"fail\" (or marked result)\n- `CLOCHE_RESULT:custom_result` marker overrides exit code\n\n### 2.2 Prompt Adapter (LLM-based agent steps)\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`\n\n**Purpose:** Invokes external coding agents (claude, etc.) with assembled prompts\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Fallback chain**: Comma-separated agent command list\n- **Command execution**: Pipes prompt to stdin, captures stdout\n- **Streaming support**: Optional real-time line-by-line output via StatusWriter\n- **Result extraction**: Searches for `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker in output\n- **Attempt tracking**: Respects `max_attempts` config, tracks in `.cloche/attempt_count/<step>/`\n- **Prompt assembly**: Combines system template, user request, validation feedback, result instructions\n- **Output logging**: Writes to `.cloche/output/<step-name>.log` and `llm-<step-name>.log`\n\n**Config Keys:**\n- `prompt`: System template (string or `file(\"path\")`)\n- `agent_command`: Comma-separated agent commands (overrides workflow-level)\n- `agent_args`: Custom arguments for agent command\n- `max_attempts`: Max retries before returning `give-up`\n- `feedback`: `\"true\"` to include prior validation output in prompt\n- `results`: Declared result names\n\n**Default Agent Args:**\n- `claude`: `-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`\n\n**Result Logic:**\n- Definitive (no fallback):\n  - Command exits 0 with output → \"success\" (or marked)\n  - Command exits non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker → marked result\n- Fallback-eligible (tries next command):\n  - Command not found (exit error without starting)\n  - Command exits non-zero without marker\n- Final fallback failure → \"fail\"\n- Max attempts reached → `give-up`\n\n**Stream Text Extraction:**\n- Parses JSON stream events (`content_block_delta` with `text_delta`)\n- Extracts final result text containing `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker\n- Accumulates text for live logging to StatusWriter\n\n---\n\n## 3. How Agents Are Configured and Selected\n\n### 3.1 Configuration Hierarchy\n\n**Workflow-level (container config):**\n```cloche\nworkflow \"name\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"claude,gemini\"\n    agent_args = \"--flag1 --flag2\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n**Step-level (overrides workflow):**\n```cloche\nstep implement {\n  agent_command = \"custom-agent\"\n  agent_args = \"--step-specific\"\n  prompt = \"Your task...\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Environment variable (highest priority):**\n- `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND`: Sets commands for all prompt steps in the run\n\n### 3.2 Configuration Resolution\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`\n\n1. Parse workflow DSL\n2. Create `PromptAdapter` with defaults: `Commands: []string{\"claude\"}`\n3. Check environment: `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` (overrides defaults)\n4. Check workflow config: `container.agent_command` (parsed by `ParseCommands()`)\n5. Per-step override: `agent_command` in step config (highest priority for that step)\n\n**ParseCommands() function:**\n```go\nfunc ParseCommands(s string) []string {\n\tparts := strings.Split(s, \",\")\n\tvar cmds []string\n\tfor _, p := range parts {\n\t\tp = strings.TrimSpace(p)\n\t\tif p != \"\" {\n\t\t\tcmds = append(cmds, p)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn cmds\n}\n```\n\n### 3.3 Step Type Detection\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\nStep type is inferred from config:\n- `prompt` key → `StepTypeAgent`\n- `run` key → `StepTypeScript`\n- `workflow_name` key → `StepTypeWorkflow`\n- Must have exactly one\n\n**Known step config keys:**\n- `prompt`, `run`, `workflow_name`, `max_attempts`, `timeout`\n- `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `results`, `feedback`, `prompt_step`\n- Plus any key prefixed with `container.`\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Agents Are Invoked During Workflow Execution\n\n### 4.1 Execution Flow\n\n**Main Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` - Workflow orchestration\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - Container-level agent runner\n\n**Flow:**\n1. **CLI invocation**: `cloche-agent <workflow-file>` (in container)\n   - File: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n   - Reads `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable\n   - Calls `Runner.Run(ctx)`\n\n2. **Runner setup**:\n   - Parses workflow DSL\n   - Creates `generic.Adapter` and `prompt.Adapter`\n   - Initializes `StatusWriter` (JSON to stdout)\n   - Creates `stepExecutor` wrapping both adapters\n   - Creates `Engine` with stepExecutor\n\n3. **Engine orchestration** (`engine.Engine.Run()`):\n   - Validates workflow (wiring, reachability)\n   - Spawns goroutines for each step\n   - Distributes results via channel\n   - Manages state and collects\n   - Main loop waits for all steps to complete\n\n4. **Step execution** (`stepExecutor.Execute()`):\n   ```\n   Switch on step.Type:\n   - StepTypeScript: generic.Adapter.Execute()\n   - StepTypeAgent with \"run\": generic.Adapter.Execute()\n   - StepTypeAgent with \"prompt\": prompt.Adapter.Execute()\n   ```\n\n5. **Status reporting**:\n   - JSON messages sent to stdout (captured by daemon)\n   - Types: `step_started`, `step_completed`, `run_completed`, `log`, `error`\n   - Protocol: `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`\n\n### 4.2 Step Execution Context\n\n**Timeout:**\n- Config: `step.Config[\"timeout\"]` (Go duration string)\n- Default: 30 minutes\n- Applied via `context.WithTimeout()` per step\n\n**Working directory:**\n- `.cloche/output/<step>.log` - Per-step output\n- `.cloche/attempt_count/<step>` - Attempt counter (for max_attempts)\n- `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` - User prompt (for prompt steps)\n- `.cloche/full.log` - Unified log with timestamps and type tags\n\n**Result validation:**\n- Engine checks that returned result is in `step.Results`\n- Failure → workflow aborts with error\n\n### 4.3 Concurrent Execution\n- Each step runs in its own goroutine\n- Multiple steps can run in parallel (fanout via wiring)\n- `collect all(...)` and `collect any(...)` synchronization\n- Results channel coordinates completion\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Files for Agent-Related Code\n\n### 5.1 Agent Runner Tests\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/agent/runner_test.go`\n\n**Key Tests:**\n- `TestRunner_CaptureWiredToStatus` - Status message flow\n- `TestRunner_WorkflowLevelAgentConfig` - Workflow-level config\n- `TestRunner_StepLevelAgentArgs` - Step-level overrides\n- `TestRunner_StepLevelOverridesWorkflowLevel` - Precedence\n- `TestRunner_FallbackChain` - Step-level fallback\n- `TestRunner_WorkflowLevelFallbackChain` - Workflow-level fallback\n- `TestRunner_UnifiedLogScriptSteps` - Mixed step logging\n- `TestRunner_UnifiedLogLLMStep` - Agent output logging\n- `TestRunner_UnifiedLogMixedSteps` - Both step types\n- `TestRunner_ExecutesWorkflowFile` - End-to-end execution\n\n### 5.2 Generic Adapter Tests\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic_test.go`\n\n**Key Tests:**\n- `TestGenericAdapter_ScriptSuccess` / `_ScriptFailure`\n- `TestGenericAdapter_ScriptModifiesFiles`\n- `TestGenericAdapter_CapturesOutput` / `_CapturesOutputOnFailure`\n- `TestGenericAdapter_StdoutMarkerOverridesExitCode`\n- `TestGenericAdapter_MarkerOverridesFailExitCode`\n\n### 5.3 Prompt Adapter Tests\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt_test.go`\n\n**Key Tests:**\n- `TestPromptAdapter_ExecutesCommand`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_IncludesFeedback` / `_NoFeedbackByDefault`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_RespectsMaxAttempts`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_CommandFailure`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_InjectsResultInstructions`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_StdoutMarkerSelectsResult`\n- `TestExecuteWritesOutputFile`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_IncrementsAttemptCount`\n- **Fallback chain tests:**\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_FallbackOnCommandNotFound`\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_FallbackOnExitErrorNoMarker`\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_NoFallbackOnMarkerResult`\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_AllCommandsFail`\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_LastCommandCrashReturnsFailResult`\n- `TestParseCommands` - Comma-separated parsing\n\n---\n\n## 6. Complete File Structure Summary\n\n### Core Files (Read-Only Exploration)\n\n**Port Definitions:**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go` - AgentAdapter interface\n\n**Agent Adapters:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` - Script executor\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` - LLM agent invoker\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt_test.go`\n\n**Orchestration:**\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - In-container orchestrator\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` - Workflow DAG executor\n\n**Domain Models:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Workflow, Step, Wire, Collect types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run, RunState, StepExecution types\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - Workflow DSL parser\n\n**Protocol & Status:**\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` - StatusWriter, StatusMessage\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go` - CLOCHE_RESULT marker extraction\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/history.go` - Execution history tracking\n\n**Entry Point:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` - Container agent binary\n\n**Example Workflows:**\n- `/workspace/examples/hello-world/build.cloche` - Script-only workflow\n- `/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/develop.cloche` - Mixed script + LLM workflow\n\n---\n\n## 7. Key Design Patterns\n\n**Port-Adapter (Hexagonal Architecture):**\n- `AgentAdapter` interface in ports\n- Multiple implementations (generic, prompt)\n- Engine operates on abstraction, not concrete types\n\n**Fallback Chain Pattern:**\n- Comma-separated agent commands\n- Tries first, falls back on not-found or non-zero without marker\n- Definitive results (with marker) stop fallback\n\n**Result Marker System:**\n- `CLOCHE_RESULT:` prefix in stdout\n- Allows agents to override exit codes\n- Stripped from logs, preserved for routing\n\n**Concurrent DAG Execution:**\n- Steps as goroutines\n- Channel-based result communication\n- Wiring + collects for synchronization\n\n**Prompt Assembly:**\n- Template (system) + user request + feedback + instructions\n- `file(\"path\")` syntax for external template files\n- Dynamic result instructions injected\n\nThis architecture enables agent-agnostic, extensible workflow execution with clear separation of concerns."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a865bb5a1f801b4bc (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63776\ntool_uses: 28\nduration_ms: 81780</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"46174c86-2501-486a-9678-0ff3d3a9d495","uuid":"a4c50ebe-f950-4326-be5c-4ebabe869a83","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand the current agent architecture. I need to know:\n\n1. The AgentAdapter interface/port definition\n2. All existing agent adapter implementations (Claude Code, Generic, etc.)\n3. How agents are configured and selected (config files, workflow DSL, etc.)\n4. How agents are invoked during workflow execution (the agent step runner)\n5. Any existing test files for agent-related code\n\nSearch in internal/ports/, internal/adapters/, internal/domain/, cmd/, and any other relevant locations. Read all relevant files completely. Provide the full file paths and key code snippets.","agentId":"a865bb5a1f801b4bc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile my comprehensive findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Agent Architecture Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase. Here's the complete agent architecture documentation:\n\n---\n\n## 1. AgentAdapter Interface/Port Definition\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`\n\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n\tName() string\n\tExecute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Simple, clean interface with only 2 methods\n- `Name()`: Returns the adapter's identifier (e.g., \"generic\", \"prompt\")\n- `Execute()`: Executes a single agent step inside a container\n  - Takes: context, step definition, and working directory\n  - Returns: step result name (string) and error\n  - Result is one of the step's declared `Results`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Existing Agent Adapter Implementations\n\n### 2.1 Generic Adapter (Script-based steps)\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`\n\n**Purpose:** Executes shell commands via `sh -c`\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Handles both `StepTypeScript` and `StepTypeAgent` with `run` config\n- Executes command in working directory\n- Captures combined stdout/stderr\n- Supports `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker in output to override exit code\n- Writes output to `.cloche/output/<step-name>.log`\n- Records execution history via `protocol.AppendHistory()`\n\n**Config Keys:**\n- `run`: Shell command to execute\n\n**Result Logic:**\n- Exit 0 + output = \"success\" (or marked result)\n- Exit non-zero = \"fail\" (or marked result)\n- `CLOCHE_RESULT:custom_result` marker overrides exit code\n\n### 2.2 Prompt Adapter (LLM-based agent steps)\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`\n\n**Purpose:** Invokes external coding agents (claude, etc.) with assembled prompts\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Fallback chain**: Comma-separated agent command list\n- **Command execution**: Pipes prompt to stdin, captures stdout\n- **Streaming support**: Optional real-time line-by-line output via StatusWriter\n- **Result extraction**: Searches for `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker in output\n- **Attempt tracking**: Respects `max_attempts` config, tracks in `.cloche/attempt_count/<step>/`\n- **Prompt assembly**: Combines system template, user request, validation feedback, result instructions\n- **Output logging**: Writes to `.cloche/output/<step-name>.log` and `llm-<step-name>.log`\n\n**Config Keys:**\n- `prompt`: System template (string or `file(\"path\")`)\n- `agent_command`: Comma-separated agent commands (overrides workflow-level)\n- `agent_args`: Custom arguments for agent command\n- `max_attempts`: Max retries before returning `give-up`\n- `feedback`: `\"true\"` to include prior validation output in prompt\n- `results`: Declared result names\n\n**Default Agent Args:**\n- `claude`: `-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`\n\n**Result Logic:**\n- Definitive (no fallback):\n  - Command exits 0 with output → \"success\" (or marked)\n  - Command exits non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker → marked result\n- Fallback-eligible (tries next command):\n  - Command not found (exit error without starting)\n  - Command exits non-zero without marker\n- Final fallback failure → \"fail\"\n- Max attempts reached → `give-up`\n\n**Stream Text Extraction:**\n- Parses JSON stream events (`content_block_delta` with `text_delta`)\n- Extracts final result text containing `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker\n- Accumulates text for live logging to StatusWriter\n\n---\n\n## 3. How Agents Are Configured and Selected\n\n### 3.1 Configuration Hierarchy\n\n**Workflow-level (container config):**\n```cloche\nworkflow \"name\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"claude,gemini\"\n    agent_args = \"--flag1 --flag2\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n**Step-level (overrides workflow):**\n```cloche\nstep implement {\n  agent_command = \"custom-agent\"\n  agent_args = \"--step-specific\"\n  prompt = \"Your task...\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Environment variable (highest priority):**\n- `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND`: Sets commands for all prompt steps in the run\n\n### 3.2 Configuration Resolution\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`\n\n1. Parse workflow DSL\n2. Create `PromptAdapter` with defaults: `Commands: []string{\"claude\"}`\n3. Check environment: `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` (overrides defaults)\n4. Check workflow config: `container.agent_command` (parsed by `ParseCommands()`)\n5. Per-step override: `agent_command` in step config (highest priority for that step)\n\n**ParseCommands() function:**\n```go\nfunc ParseCommands(s string) []string {\n\tparts := strings.Split(s, \",\")\n\tvar cmds []string\n\tfor _, p := range parts {\n\t\tp = strings.TrimSpace(p)\n\t\tif p != \"\" {\n\t\t\tcmds = append(cmds, p)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn cmds\n}\n```\n\n### 3.3 Step Type Detection\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\nStep type is inferred from config:\n- `prompt` key → `StepTypeAgent`\n- `run` key → `StepTypeScript`\n- `workflow_name` key → `StepTypeWorkflow`\n- Must have exactly one\n\n**Known step config keys:**\n- `prompt`, `run`, `workflow_name`, `max_attempts`, `timeout`\n- `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `results`, `feedback`, `prompt_step`\n- Plus any key prefixed with `container.`\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Agents Are Invoked During Workflow Execution\n\n### 4.1 Execution Flow\n\n**Main Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` - Workflow orchestration\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - Container-level agent runner\n\n**Flow:**\n1. **CLI invocation**: `cloche-agent <workflow-file>` (in container)\n   - File: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n   - Reads `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable\n   - Calls `Runner.Run(ctx)`\n\n2. **Runner setup**:\n   - Parses workflow DSL\n   - Creates `generic.Adapter` and `prompt.Adapter`\n   - Initializes `StatusWriter` (JSON to stdout)\n   - Creates `stepExecutor` wrapping both adapters\n   - Creates `Engine` with stepExecutor\n\n3. **Engine orchestration** (`engine.Engine.Run()`):\n   - Validates workflow (wiring, reachability)\n   - Spawns goroutines for each step\n   - Distributes results via channel\n   - Manages state and collects\n   - Main loop waits for all steps to complete\n\n4. **Step execution** (`stepExecutor.Execute()`):\n   ```\n   Switch on step.Type:\n   - StepTypeScript: generic.Adapter.Execute()\n   - StepTypeAgent with \"run\": generic.Adapter.Execute()\n   - StepTypeAgent with \"prompt\": prompt.Adapter.Execute()\n   ```\n\n5. **Status reporting**:\n   - JSON messages sent to stdout (captured by daemon)\n   - Types: `step_started`, `step_completed`, `run_completed`, `log`, `error`\n   - Protocol: `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`\n\n### 4.2 Step Execution Context\n\n**Timeout:**\n- Config: `step.Config[\"timeout\"]` (Go duration string)\n- Default: 30 minutes\n- Applied via `context.WithTimeout()` per step\n\n**Working directory:**\n- `.cloche/output/<step>.log` - Per-step output\n- `.cloche/attempt_count/<step>` - Attempt counter (for max_attempts)\n- `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` - User prompt (for prompt steps)\n- `.cloche/full.log` - Unified log with timestamps and type tags\n\n**Result validation:**\n- Engine checks that returned result is in `step.Results`\n- Failure → workflow aborts with error\n\n### 4.3 Concurrent Execution\n- Each step runs in its own goroutine\n- Multiple steps can run in parallel (fanout via wiring)\n- `collect all(...)` and `collect any(...)` synchronization\n- Results channel coordinates completion\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Files for Agent-Related Code\n\n### 5.1 Agent Runner Tests\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/agent/runner_test.go`\n\n**Key Tests:**\n- `TestRunner_CaptureWiredToStatus` - Status message flow\n- `TestRunner_WorkflowLevelAgentConfig` - Workflow-level config\n- `TestRunner_StepLevelAgentArgs` - Step-level overrides\n- `TestRunner_StepLevelOverridesWorkflowLevel` - Precedence\n- `TestRunner_FallbackChain` - Step-level fallback\n- `TestRunner_WorkflowLevelFallbackChain` - Workflow-level fallback\n- `TestRunner_UnifiedLogScriptSteps` - Mixed step logging\n- `TestRunner_UnifiedLogLLMStep` - Agent output logging\n- `TestRunner_UnifiedLogMixedSteps` - Both step types\n- `TestRunner_ExecutesWorkflowFile` - End-to-end execution\n\n### 5.2 Generic Adapter Tests\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic_test.go`\n\n**Key Tests:**\n- `TestGenericAdapter_ScriptSuccess` / `_ScriptFailure`\n- `TestGenericAdapter_ScriptModifiesFiles`\n- `TestGenericAdapter_CapturesOutput` / `_CapturesOutputOnFailure`\n- `TestGenericAdapter_StdoutMarkerOverridesExitCode`\n- `TestGenericAdapter_MarkerOverridesFailExitCode`\n\n### 5.3 Prompt Adapter Tests\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt_test.go`\n\n**Key Tests:**\n- `TestPromptAdapter_ExecutesCommand`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_IncludesFeedback` / `_NoFeedbackByDefault`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_RespectsMaxAttempts`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_CommandFailure`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_InjectsResultInstructions`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_StdoutMarkerSelectsResult`\n- `TestExecuteWritesOutputFile`\n- `TestPromptAdapter_IncrementsAttemptCount`\n- **Fallback chain tests:**\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_FallbackOnCommandNotFound`\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_FallbackOnExitErrorNoMarker`\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_NoFallbackOnMarkerResult`\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_AllCommandsFail`\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_LastCommandCrashReturnsFailResult`\n- `TestParseCommands` - Comma-separated parsing\n\n---\n\n## 6. Complete File Structure Summary\n\n### Core Files (Read-Only Exploration)\n\n**Port Definitions:**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go` - AgentAdapter interface\n\n**Agent Adapters:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` - Script executor\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` - LLM agent invoker\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt_test.go`\n\n**Orchestration:**\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - In-container orchestrator\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` - Workflow DAG executor\n\n**Domain Models:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Workflow, Step, Wire, Collect types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run, RunState, StepExecution types\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - Workflow DSL parser\n\n**Protocol & Status:**\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` - StatusWriter, StatusMessage\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go` - CLOCHE_RESULT marker extraction\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/history.go` - Execution history tracking\n\n**Entry Point:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` - Container agent binary\n\n**Example Workflows:**\n- `/workspace/examples/hello-world/build.cloche` - Script-only workflow\n- `/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/develop.cloche` - Mixed script + LLM workflow\n\n---\n\n## 7. Key Design Patterns\n\n**Port-Adapter (Hexagonal Architecture):**\n- `AgentAdapter` interface in ports\n- Multiple implementations (generic, prompt)\n- Engine operates on abstraction, not concrete types\n\n**Fallback Chain Pattern:**\n- Comma-separated agent commands\n- Tries first, falls back on not-found or non-zero without marker\n- Definitive results (with marker) stop fallback\n\n**Result Marker System:**\n- `CLOCHE_RESULT:` prefix in stdout\n- Allows agents to override exit codes\n- Stripped from logs, preserved for routing\n\n**Concurrent DAG Execution:**\n- Steps as goroutines\n- Channel-based result communication\n- Wiring + collects for synchronization\n\n**Prompt Assembly:**\n- Template (system) + user request + feedback + instructions\n- `file(\"path\")` syntax for external template files\n- Dynamic result instructions injected\n\nThis architecture enables agent-agnostic, extensible workflow execution with clear separation of concerns."}],"totalDurationMs":81780,"totalTokens":63776,"totalToolUseCount":28,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":704,"cache_read_input_tokens":59598,"output_tokens":3471,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":704},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
