[2026-03-07T16:38:02Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MAcKoZM5SuFRpy6GQ3hKxv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze what already exists and what the task requires:\n\n**Already exists:**\n1. Fallback chains via comma-separated `agent_command` (e.g., `agent_command = \"claude,gemini\"`)\n2. Per-step `agent_command` overrides\n3. Workflow-level `container.agent_command` config\n4. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` env var override\n5. `defaultAgentArgs` map for known agents (only `claude` currently)\n6. Fallback logic: tries next command on not-found or exit-error-without-marker\n\n\n7. Several gaps that need addressing: only `claude` has default args defined, while `gemini` and `codex` lack them; the step executor mutates the shared `prompt.Adapter` during per-step overrides which creates a race condition for parallel execution; there's no visibility into which agent actually ran or when fallbacks occurred; and the fallback chain doesn't support per-command arguments like different settings for claude versus gemini.\n\nThe most impactful improvements would be expanding default args across all supported agents and fixing the mutation issue that breaks parallel steps. switching trivial\n2. **Fix the race condition** in stepExecutor where per-step overrides mutate the shared adapter\n3. **Log which agent command was used** (and which were tried) during fallback\n4. **Support per-agent args in the chain** via a syntax like `claude --flag,gemini --other-flag` or better, a map-like config\n\nActually, looking at the current code more carefully:\n\nThe step executor in runner.go mutates `e.prompt.Commands` and `e.prompt.ExplicitArgs` directly for each step. This is a race condition if steps execute in parallel! This is a real bug that needs fixing.\n\nFor simplifying agent switching, here's what I'll do:\n\n1. **Add default args for known agents** (gemini, codex) so users only need to change the command name\n2. **Fix the race condition** by creating per-step adapter copies or passing overrides differently\n3. **Log fallback attempts** so users can see which agent was tried\n4. **Support per-command explicit args** via the `agent_args` map syntax (e.g., `agent_args.claude`, `agent_args.gemini`)\n\nThe fallback chain already works, so the real priorities are adding default args for more agents so switching is seamless, fixing that step-level override bug that could cause issues with parallel execution, and making sure users get visibility into which agent actually ran when fallbacks happen.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16219,"cache_read_input_tokens":28677,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16219},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"46174c86-2501-486a-9678-0ff3d3a9d495","uuid":"7032d552-5898-4770-b2dd-fa92683dc7c3"}
